interestingcomments.content: Once an image has been digitally rendered, whether it has been manipulated or not, it has exited the traditional. . I think painters have said the very same some 100 years ago when photography got a hold with a broader audience. "Once an image has not been rendered by the touch of a paint brush, whether it has been manipulated or not, it has exited the traditional." The means how an image is created are irrelevant. The amount of deviating from the original image by means of processing, altering the image after it has been taken are relevant. For some this means one should shoot in JPG and have set white balance and exposure to perfection in camera, for others it simply means that cloning heads, erasing content and altering the meaning of an image are passé.
